You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React 19, Shadcn UI, Radix, and Tailwind.

This is a pnpm monorepo for StartupKit - a SaaS framework with CLI, npm packages, and scaffolding templates.

## Key Architecture

- `packages/*` → Published npm packages (`@startupkit/*`)
- `templates/repo/packages/*` → Template workspace packages (`@repo/*`)  
- `templates/next/` → Next.js template that imports from `@repo/*`

## Code Style

- Write concise TypeScript - no `any` keyword ever
- Use `interface` over `type` for object shapes
- Use `function` keyword for pure functions
- Avoid enums - use const objects with `as const`
- No unnecessary comments - code should be self-documenting
- Formatting: tabs, double quotes, no trailing commas, semicolons as needed

## React/Next.js

- Prefer Server Components - minimize `"use client"`
- Wrap client components in Suspense with fallback
- Use `nuqs` for URL state management
- Dynamic imports for non-critical components

## Templates Rule

- Never add auth config to `templates/next/` - it imports from `@repo/auth`
- Auth routes: `app/auth/[...all]/` NOT `app/api/auth/[...all]/`
- Use workspace packages: `@repo/auth`, `@repo/ui`, `@repo/db`

## Commands

- `pnpm dev` - Start dev servers
- `pnpm lint:fix` - Auto-fix linting
- `pnpm typecheck` - Type-check all
- `pnpm with-env <cmd>` - Run with env vars
- `pnpm db:generate` / `pnpm db:migrate` - Database migrations

## Never

- Use `any` type
- Add unnecessary comments
- Publish to npm (humans only)
- Create duplicate config in templates/next
